<subSubSection id="05F737575695C6C7779424774EF1D069" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="01ADD92C5EA9D9219394CE4550EC0D82" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7FE7971CEC35D3A2CB2F918B167C8426" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Carapace (
<figureCitation id="54ECB222F757394938034EA6564F5C73" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Metaplax elegans De Man, 1888 (A-C NCHUZOOL 15496, male, 12.7 mm), M. longipes Stimpson, 1858 (D-F ZRC 2019.0581, male, 14.9 mm), M. sheni Gordon, 1930 (G-I NCHUZOOL 15466, male, 9.9 mm), and M. tredecim Tweedie, 1950 (J-L paratype, ZRC 1964.7.14.4 - 18, 16.2 mm). A, D, G, J, A carapace B, E, H, K left infraorbital ridge C, F, I, L outer view of right cheliped. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.877.38300.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/343945" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.877.38300.figure2">Figs 2J</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="FC7AC3BB86BD631798729ACCC1D167C8" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Metaplax tredecim Tweedie, 1950. A, F Dorsal view B ventral view C left infraorbital ridge D right cheliped E right side of carapace showing the five teeth of lateral margin. A-E paratype male (CW 16.2 mm; ZRC 1964.7.14.4 - 18; Labuan) F male (CW 16.5 mm; NCHUZOOL 15473; Hong Kong) G male (CW 15.4 mm; NCHUZOOL 15475; Labuan, Malaysia) H, I male (18.2 mm; NCHUZOOL 15705; Hong Kong) G-I color in life. Scale bars: 2.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.877.38300.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/343949" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.877.38300.figure6">6A, F, G</figureCitation>
) subquadrate, 1.35 times broader than long (
<emphasis id="369CA45B6945DFBD2ED046009AD8A25E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">N</emphasis>
= 39, SD = 0.03), regions defined by shallow grooves, slightly inflated, surface pitted; front nearly straight, medially slightly concave; lateral margin mildly convex, posteriorly converging, cut into five teeth, anterior two pronounced, quadrate, posterior two inconspicuous; posterolateral facet slightly depressed, behind second notch decorated with two short oblique granular ridges. Infraorbital ridge (
<figureCitation id="E7FF809A70591367D7D1BA19995FCC3A" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Metaplax elegans De Man, 1888 (A-C NCHUZOOL 15496, male, 12.7 mm), M. longipes Stimpson, 1858 (D-F ZRC 2019.0581, male, 14.9 mm), M. sheni Gordon, 1930 (G-I NCHUZOOL 15466, male, 9.9 mm), and M. tredecim Tweedie, 1950 (J-L paratype, ZRC 1964.7.14.4 - 18, 16.2 mm). A, D, G, J, A carapace B, E, H, K left infraorbital ridge C, F, I, L outer view of right cheliped. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.877.38300.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/343945" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.877.38300.figure2">Figs 2K</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="F0C281DE8744F6BF92752B0E13EE27C0" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Metaplax tredecim Tweedie, 1950. A, F Dorsal view B ventral view C left infraorbital ridge D right cheliped E right side of carapace showing the five teeth of lateral margin. A-E paratype male (CW 16.2 mm; ZRC 1964.7.14.4 - 18; Labuan) F male (CW 16.5 mm; NCHUZOOL 15473; Hong Kong) G male (CW 15.4 mm; NCHUZOOL 15475; Labuan, Malaysia) H, I male (18.2 mm; NCHUZOOL 15705; Hong Kong) G-I color in life. Scale bars: 2.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.877.38300.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/343949" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.877.38300.figure6">6C</figureCitation>
) markedly sexually dimorphic: in males medial four or five roughly same size, decreasing in breadth laterally, laterally of a row of seven or eight small, rounded, isomorphic, tubercles; females with 21-27 small isomorphic tubercles. Chelipeds (
<figureCitation id="94B3DB54FCC26FA18D10B189A0D0B259" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Metaplax elegans De Man, 1888 (A-C NCHUZOOL 15496, male, 12.7 mm), M. longipes Stimpson, 1858 (D-F ZRC 2019.0581, male, 14.9 mm), M. sheni Gordon, 1930 (G-I NCHUZOOL 15466, male, 9.9 mm), and M. tredecim Tweedie, 1950 (J-L paratype, ZRC 1964.7.14.4 - 18, 16.2 mm). A, D, G, J, A carapace B, E, H, K left infraorbital ridge C, F, I, L outer view of right cheliped. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.877.38300.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/343945" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.877.38300.figure2">Figs 2L</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="98651AD57DBF190C7CE984721D041B9E" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Metaplax tredecim Tweedie, 1950. A, F Dorsal view B ventral view C left infraorbital ridge D right cheliped E right side of carapace showing the five teeth of lateral margin. A-E paratype male (CW 16.2 mm; ZRC 1964.7.14.4 - 18; Labuan) F male (CW 16.5 mm; NCHUZOOL 15473; Hong Kong) G male (CW 15.4 mm; NCHUZOOL 15475; Labuan, Malaysia) H, I male (18.2 mm; NCHUZOOL 15705; Hong Kong) G-I color in life. Scale bars: 2.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.877.38300.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/343949" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.877.38300.figure6">6D</figureCitation>
) stout, symmetrical, palm 2.3 times longer than broad, length of palm approximately 1.6 times of length of dactyl (
<emphasis id="6932A95EB181BC44F80D54931B21CEA8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">N</emphasis>
= 12), meri slightly dilated anteriorly, lined with minute denticles along the margin; chela surface finely granulated, along cutting edges both fingers unarmed. Ambulatory legs slender, elongated, meri of P3 and P4 tomentum-covered on distal half, and propodi of P2 to P4 with thick mat of setae. G1 (
<figureCitation id="6006BE4171445F64193358A498E87092" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Metaplax elegans De Man, 1888 (A-D NCHUZOOL 15496, male, 12.7 mm), right G 1; M. longipes Stimpson, 1858 (E-H ZRC 2019.0581, male, 14.9 mm), right G 1; M. sheni Gordon, 1930 (I-L NCHUZOOL 15466, male, 9.9 mm), right G 1; and M. tredecim Tweedie, 1950 (M-P paratype, ZRC 1964.7.14.4 - 18, 16.2 mm), left G 1. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A-H, M-P); 0.2 mm (I-L)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.877.38300.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/343950" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.877.38300.figure7">
Fig. 7
<normalizedToken id="90F3953BE1B3CE07146D3F1CB9CDF23D" originalValue="M–P">M-P</normalizedToken>
</figureCitation>
) elongated, slender, almost straight.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A98BE72239FAA493AB14E02DD91B7BE2" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="67744B38F60F311EE4E26987C79A1E09" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="815E2A170C25454AEC17D0935FFFB75C" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Southeast and East Asia: northern Borneo (Labuan, Malaysia; Brunei), Vietnam (Quang Ninh; Khanh Hoa), and South China (Hong Kong) (
<figureCitation id="842BD0CAB411C270396C42262123E464" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Collection sites (solid symbols) for species of the genus Metaplax used in this study: green rhombus for M. elegans; red circles for M. longipes; blue triangles for M. sheni; and purple squares for M. tredecim. Empty symbols mean the additional records from references (see synonym lists for each species)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.877.38300.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/343944" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.877.38300.figure1">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="85D107AF7401D6AE6E120D4293DB0AD7" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="habitat">
<paragraph id="206470171EC103C68308A6EC63A68E40" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="82013DD8B9C7D7BC6BFF4F2EBA1EBE2F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
In Hong Kong, in comparison to 
<taxonomicName id="3ADFAE161CC81AE58B3898772B0F4C1B" genus="M." lsidName="M. longipes" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="longipes">
<emphasis id="68F42221EE2FFE62147A71063DCEB501" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M. longipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="716A02B1BD443279268528F8A2454EBD" genus="M." lsidName="M. tredecim" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="tredecim">
<emphasis id="CE8A8A4DBAD0E6D18059BE8E23DD1D5B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M. tredecim</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
tends to occur in habitats of coarser, grittier substrates, with less freshwater input, and frequently on open sandflats rather unsheltered by mangroves.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4A200EADD6718F4AE7AB3CB5BA745122" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="B86E7C8AA94461E2999AE041BB2F0AB2" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EE12E3FD58675B441D25A00AEBCEB2C1" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Identification of the 
<taxonomicName id="B5398E0B02C67CAD4D80BF2C47B28239" class="Malacostraca" family="Varunidae" genus="Metaplax" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Metaplax tredecim" order="Decapoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tredecim">
<emphasis id="9B6919297BCC9A7B450704E50FC199DD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Metaplax tredecim</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
had been confusing, particularly based on the number of teeth along the lateral margin of the carapace. 
<bibRefCitation id="790814D9976533E13A8FD690F45EF026" author="Tweedie, MWF" journalOrPublisher="Sarawak Museum Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="338 - 369" refId="B85" refString="Tweedie, MWF, 1950. Grapsoid crabs from Labuan and Sarawak. Sarawak Museum Journal 5: 338 - 369" title="Grapsoid crabs from Labuan and Sarawak." volume="5" year="1950">Tweedie (1950</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 6) showed merely three conspicuous lobes, the posterior one occupying more than half of carapace length. However, as noted by 
<bibRefCitation id="4DE2D0C1243C21669B634994D80F5B2E" author="Davie, PJF" journalOrPublisher="Raffles Bulletin of Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="379 - 386" refId="B15" refString="Davie, PJF, Nguyen, VX, 2003. A new species of Metaplax (Crustacea: Brachyura: Varunidae: Cyclograpsinae) from Vietnam. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology 51: 379 - 386" title="A new species of Metaplax (Crustacea: Brachyura: Varunidae: Cyclograpsinae) from Vietnam." volume="51" year="2003">Davie and Nguyen (2003)</bibRefCitation>
, members of the genus often have the structures around the posterolateral facet obscured by setae-trapped sediments, and not visible unless carefully denuded. Reexamination of a paratype male (16.2 mm; ZRC 1964.7.14.4-18), after denudation, showed the lateral margin to be interrupted by 4 notches (hence 5 teeth) (
<figureCitation id="BE5A55CBD4CFAD143E43C6BC57FCC990" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Metaplax elegans De Man, 1888 (A-C NCHUZOOL 15496, male, 12.7 mm), M. longipes Stimpson, 1858 (D-F ZRC 2019.0581, male, 14.9 mm), M. sheni Gordon, 1930 (G-I NCHUZOOL 15466, male, 9.9 mm), and M. tredecim Tweedie, 1950 (J-L paratype, ZRC 1964.7.14.4 - 18, 16.2 mm). A, D, G, J, A carapace B, E, H, K left infraorbital ridge C, F, I, L outer view of right cheliped. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.877.38300.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/343945" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.877.38300.figure2">Figs 2J</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="424CABFC148D069E9A739D6DF72E2D8D" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Metaplax tredecim Tweedie, 1950. A, F Dorsal view B ventral view C left infraorbital ridge D right cheliped E right side of carapace showing the five teeth of lateral margin. A-E paratype male (CW 16.2 mm; ZRC 1964.7.14.4 - 18; Labuan) F male (CW 16.5 mm; NCHUZOOL 15473; Hong Kong) G male (CW 15.4 mm; NCHUZOOL 15475; Labuan, Malaysia) H, I male (18.2 mm; NCHUZOOL 15705; Hong Kong) G-I color in life. Scale bars: 2.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.877.38300.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/343949" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.877.38300.figure6">6A, E</figureCitation>
), the posterior two being inconspicuously defined by the last notch.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="944CD4238DBFDAC3347A96AF064BFB8A" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
As mentioned above, two forms, differing in the number of tubercles or lobes on the infraorbital ridge, were recognized in specimens identified with 
<taxonomicName id="A628D0B7A12F76E470F96FFFE93D1A2B" genus="M." lsidName="M. longipes" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="longipes">
<emphasis id="EBDEE79AB42F9C15BF213A7B5A33B714" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M. longipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="12CAA3B7D827B74775951F65AFD5AA4F" author="Dai, AY" journalOrPublisher="China Ocean Press, Beijing" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B13" refString="Dai, AY, Yang, SL, Song, YZ, Chen, GX, 1986. Crabs of the China seas. China Ocean Press, Beijing" title="Crabs of the China seas." year="1986">Dai et al. (1986)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="B41DB1F4D30128BABF4AAAD40A2C5E94" author="Dai, AY" journalOrPublisher="China Ocean Press, Beijing" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B12" refString="Dai, AY, Yang, SL, 1991. Crabs of the China Seas. China Ocean Press, Beijing" title="Crabs of the China Seas." year="1991">Dai and Yang (1991)</bibRefCitation>
. We confirmed that specimens from the study area, characterized by the possession of about 17 tubercles or lobes closely represent 
<taxonomicName id="B281E3A758789747F5615785ED3355B2" genus="M." lsidName="M. tredecim" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="tredecim">
<emphasis id="A7DEEC652FB335066AF4A345526F477A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M. tredecim</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. There is little doubt that the material studied by 
<bibRefCitation id="AFC8564F17629D6BA4BE6DD326C1E2AF" author="Dai, AY" journalOrPublisher="China Ocean Press, Beijing" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B13" refString="Dai, AY, Yang, SL, Song, YZ, Chen, GX, 1986. Crabs of the China seas. China Ocean Press, Beijing" title="Crabs of the China seas." year="1986">Dai et al. (1986)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="2A8821B4B6E1B9D88E0BCB410D01A64E" author="Dai, AY" journalOrPublisher="China Ocean Press, Beijing" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B12" refString="Dai, AY, Yang, SL, 1991. Crabs of the China Seas. China Ocean Press, Beijing" title="Crabs of the China Seas." year="1991">Dai and Yang (1991)</bibRefCitation>
included two species, 
<taxonomicName id="75E76FC5CD8D0287670C29B1900151B9" genus="M." lsidName="M. longipes" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="longipes">
<emphasis id="DD45902EDD7B1A2915097D0F33C932E0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M. longipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="92B1F9AF4E4E668DD0C7ED8C7F0CD093" genus="M." lsidName="M. tredecim" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="tredecim">
<emphasis id="9CE5B95F3DC9DDCB1A1CADA3E26FCCFF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M. tredecim</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4CE91846E17700363A9F88E239F350AA" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<bibRefCitation id="A5C38B4CEAD97D608078E0B50872536F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B8">Chertoprud et al. (2012)</bibRefCitation>
recorded &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="F9374522D1DA7F692ACAA6B1DCE83542" genus="M." lsidName="M. longipes" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="longipes">
<emphasis id="58635666D92A7500EBB82CBDE740CFB7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M. longipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; from Nha Phu, southeastern Vietnam. However, given the infraorbital ridge with 17 tubercles and the chelipeds with the length of palm/the length of dactyl ratio about 1.5 (estimated from their plate 47F on page 295), this record is suspected to represent 
<taxonomicName id="77BFEDA0AEE0A1B160946AB9A9DF7370" genus="M." lsidName="M. tredecim" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="tredecim">
<emphasis id="B271D17B7EAE46402519E7E65264D5E5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M. tredecim</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
instead (see Table 
<tableCitation id="4B67E8A6E23E2B0A00538475A1886DC9" captionStartId="T2" httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/2CCAB3CE4375FA31438947C2ED9CEA7C" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableUuid="2CCAB3CE4375FA31438947C2ED9CEA7C">2</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
